  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc2\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 10\u0d9a \u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A proposal of 10 points from Harsha to recover the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In order to recover the country from the current economic crisis in the short term and in the medium term, he recently presented to the Parliament the economic program \"Getting rid of the debt trap and the plan for inclusive sustainable development\" compiled by the Member of Parliament, Dr. Harsha De Silva, and this morning (14) He informed the media.",
        "There, he mentioned that this economic plan has been prepared by identifying 10 major areas that need to be reformed.",
        "Credit crisis management, fiscal and exchange rate policy, revenue stabilization, expenditure control, public sector management, energy and public utilities, trade, industry, agriculture and services promotion, factor market reforms, strong social safety net, transparency and accountability. Includes.",
        "This economic plan prepared by Dr. Harsha de Silva has been approved by the economic policy unit of the main opposition party, the People's Force. Member of Parliament Mr. Kabir Hashim and Mr. Iran Wickramaratne of the Economic Response Unit of Samagi Jana Balawega have also participated in creating this economic plan and Professor Premachandra Athukorala has also given advice for this.",
        "Also, this is based on the proposals of 08 groups by the National Movement for Social Justice (Advocata Institute, Sri Lanka Bar Association, Elle Gunawamsa Thero, Independent Economists, National Movement for Social Justice, NPP, SJB, Group 43) and Sri The views of the CFP and business groups have also been consulted and compiled.",
        "\u201cThis is a short and medium term economic plan. When Mr. Dallas Alahapperuma came forward as the presidential candidate, I was entrusted with the responsibility of building this in consultation with the opposition parties. Many opposition parties have approved this. Therefore, I emphasize to the government to implement this program immediately. Generally, the government should present such a program.",
        "We don't have time to talk about parties and opposition. This economic plan is prepared by experts. So, implement this immediately. Or, the government will present their economic plan. We don't have time to waste.\"",
        "This economic plan also includes proposals to restore loss-making government institutions, and Dr. Harsha de Silva, commenting on that, said that at this time, to recover the country, we will have to drink bitter medicine."
      ],
